**What is Fertility?**
- Fertility is being able to conceive a child
| Infertility means not being able to get pregnant after trying for 1 year
| For women over 35, it's 6 months of trying

**The Menstrual Cycle and Fertility:**
- Your cycle is when you're most fertile
| Ovulation is when an egg is released from the ovary |
| This happens about once a month |
| You can get pregnant around the time of ovulation

**When Are You Most Fertile?**
- About 2 weeks before your period starts
| This is called your "fertile window" |
| The egg lives for about 12-24 hours |
| Sperm can live inside the body for up to 5 days |

**Things That Affect Fertility:**

**For Women:**
- Age (fertility decreases after age 35)
| Weight (too high or too low) |
| Smoking and alcohol |
| Stress
| Certain medical conditions

**For Men:**
- Age (though less than women)
| Smoking and alcohol |
| Weight
| Heat exposure to testicles |
| Certain medical conditions

**When to See a Doctor:**
| Under 35 and trying for 1 year |
| 35 or older and trying for 6 months |
| Known fertility issues |
| Irregular or no periods |

**Remember:** Many fertility problems are treatable. If you're concerned, talk to a healthcare provider.`,
