      content: `Understanding fertility requires knowledge of the menstrual cycle, ovulation, and factors that affect reproductive capacity.

**The Menstrual Cycle and Fertility:**

**Cycle Phases:**

| Phase | Days | Fertility Status |
|-------|------|------------------|
| Menstruation | 1-5 | Low fertility |
| Follicular | 6-13 | Increasing fertility |
| Ovulation | 14 | Peak fertility |
| Luteal | 15-28 | Low fertility |

**Ovulation:**
- Egg release from ovary
| Usually day 14 of a 28-day cycle |
| Egg survives 12-24 hours |
| Sperm survives up to 5 days |
| Fertile window: 5 days before ovulation to 1 day after |

**Tracking Ovulation:**

**Calendar Method:**
- Track cycle length for several months
| Ovulation ≈ 14 days before next period |
| Less reliable for irregular cycles |

**Basal Body Temperature:**
- Temperature rises slightly after ovulation
| Take temperature every morning before getting out of bed |
| Best for confirming ovulation after it happens

**Ovulation Predictor Kits:**
| Detect LH surge in urine |
| Predict ovulation 12-36 hours before |
| Most accurate over-the-counter method

**Cervical Mucus Changes:**
- Clear, stretchy mucus = fertile
| Thick, cloudy mucus = less fertile |

**Fertility Awareness:**
- Combines multiple tracking methods
| Can be used to achieve or avoid pregnancy |
| Requires training and practice

**Factors Affecting Fertility:**

**Age-Related Decline:**

| Age (Women) | Monthly Fertility Rate |
|-------------|----------------------|
| 20 | 20-25% |
| 30 | 15-20% |
| 35 | 10-15% |
| 40 | <5% |

**Lifestyle Factors:**

**Negative Impacts:**
- Smoking (reduces egg quality)
| Excessive alcohol |
| Caffeine (>200 mg/day) |
| Being very over- or underweight
| Extreme exercise
| Chronic stress

**Positive Impacts:**
- Balanced diet
| Regular moderate exercise |
