**Definitions:**

**Infertility:**
- Inability to conceive after 12 months of unprotected intercourse
| 6 months if female partner ≥35 years |
| Or inability to carry a pregnancy to live birth

**Primary Infertility:**
| Never achieved a pregnancy

**Secondary Infertility:**
| Previous pregnancy but unable to conceive again

**Initial Evaluation:**

**Both Partners:**
- Comprehensive medical history
| Physical examination |
| Lifestyle assessment |
| Frequency and timing of intercourse

**Female Evaluation:**

**History:**
| Menstrual history (regularity, symptoms) |
| Obstetric history |
| Surgical history |
| Pelvic infection history |
| Medications and exposures |
| Family history

**Laboratory Assessment:**

**Day 3 Labs:**
| FSH: Ovarian reserve (normal <10-12 mIU/mL) |
| LH: LH/FSH ratio (elevated in PCOS) |
| Estradiol: Ovarian function |
| AMH: Ovarian reserve (normal 1-4 ng/mL) |
| TSH: Thyroid function |
| Prolactin: Exclude hyperprolactinemia

**Ovulation Assessment:**
| BBT charts |
| Ovulation predictor kits |
| Mid-luteal progesterone (>3 ng/mL confirms ovulation) |
| Serial ultrasounds

**Tubal and Uterine Evaluation:**

**Hysterosalpingography (HSG):**
| X-ray with contrast dye |
| Evaluates:
  - Tubal patency
  - Uterine cavity shape |
  - Proximal/distal tubal blockage |

**Sonohysterogram:**
| Saline infusion ultrasound |
| Evaluates uterine cavity for:
  - Polyps
  - Fibroids
  - Scar tissue |

**Diagnostic Laparoscopy:**
| Direct visualization |
| Treat endometriosis, adhesions |
| Gold standard for tubal evaluation (rarely used now)

