**In Vitro Fertilization Advanced Techniques:**

**Intracytoplasmic Sperm Injection (ICSI):**

**Indications:**
- Severe male factor
| Previous fertilization failure |
| Azoospermia (surgical retrieval) |

**Technique:**
| Single sperm injected into each egg |
| Bypasses natural barriers |

**Outcomes:**
| Fertilization rates: 70-80% |
| Similar pregnancy rates to standard IVF |

**Assisted Hatching:**
| Opening in zona pellucida before transfer |
| Theorized to improve implantation |
| Evidence for selected cases only |

**Preimplantation Genetic Testing:**

**PGT-A (Aneuploidy):**
| Screens for chromosomal number abnormalities |
| Mosaicism detection |
| Improves implantation rates in selected populations
| Reduces miscarriage rates

**PGT-M (Monogenic):**
| Testing for specific genetic mutations |
| Single gene disorders (cystic fibrosis, SMA) |
| Requires probe development

**PGT-SR (Structural Rearrangements):**
| Translocations, inversions |
| Reduces miscarriage risk

